	10 directories, 33 files

Copy top level executable script.

   cp _tmp_scons/scons.py scons

Which will fail.

    $ ./scons
    SCons import failed. Unable to find engine files in:
      /home/anatoli/g/godot/src/..
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "/home/anatoli/g/godot/src/./scons", line 89, in <module>
        import SCons.Script
    ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'SCons'

Add necessary directory structure and copy files one by one.

    mkdir -p .scons/SCons/Script
    cp _tmp_scons/scons-local-4.3.0/SCons/Script/__init__.py .scons/SCons/Script/__init__.py

Set SCONS_LIB_DIR (patch it later) to `.scons` where files are.

    $ SCONS_LIB_DIR=.scons ./scons
    SCons import failed. Unable to find engine files in:
      .scons
      /home/anatoli/g/godot/src/..
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "/home/anatoli/g/godot/src/./scons", line 89, in <module>
        import SCons.Script
      File "/home/anatoli/g/godot/src/.scons/SCons/Script/__init__.py", line 71, in <module>
        import SCons.Action
    ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'SCons.Action'

Copy the rest.

    cp _tmp_scons/scons-local-4.3.0/SCons/Action.py .scons/SCons

